<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Home</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: #111;
            color: #fff;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
            text-align: center;
            text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 28px;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }

        .content {
            /* max-width: 600px; */
            margin-bottom: 30px;
            display: flex;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            justify-content: center;
        }

        .csrf-info {
            width: 250px;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #222;
            color: #fff;
            border-radius: 5px;
            margin: 10px;
        }

        p {
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        form {
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }

        input[type="email"] {
            padding: 10px;
            width: 250px;
            border: none;
            background-color: #222;
            color: #fff;
            border-radius: 5px;
            margin-right: 10px;
        }

        button {
            padding: 10px 20px;
            border: none;
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            color: #fff;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
        }

        button:hover {
            background-color: #45a049;
        }

        a {
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        .corner {
            position: fixed;
            bottom: 20px;
            right: 20px;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: flex-end;
        }

        .corner a {
            display: inline-block;
            color: #fff;
            font-size: 16px;
            margin: 5px;
            text-decoration: none;
            transition: color 0.3s ease;
        }

        .corner a:hover {
            color: #4CAF50;
            text-decoration: underline;
        }

        .social-icons {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            margin-top: 30px;
        }

        .social-icons a {
            display: inline-block;
            margin: 0 10px;
            color: #fff;
            font-size: 24px;
            text-decoration: none;
            transition: color 0.3s ease;
        }

        .social-icons a:hover {
            color: #4CAF50;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Welcome to the Home Page</h1>
    <a href="/profile"><button> Profile</button></a>

    <div class="content">
        <div class="csrf-info">
            <h3>CSRF Information 1</h3>
            <p>CSRF (Cross-Site Request Forgery) is a security vulnerability that allows an attacker to trick a user's browser into performing undesired actions on a trusted website.</p>
            <p>To prevent CSRF attacks, it's important to implement countermeasures such as:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Using CSRF tokens</li>
                <li>Verifying the Referer header</li>
                <li>Using same-origin policy</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="csrf-info">
            <h3>CSRF Information 2</h3>
            <p>CSRF attacks can lead to severe consequences, such as unauthorized actions, data manipulation, and account compromise.</p>
            <p>By following secure coding practices and implementing proper CSRF protection, the risk of CSRF attacks can be significantly reduced.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="csrf-info">
            <h3>CSRF Information 3</h3>
            <p>Preventing CSRF attacks involves validating and verifying requests to ensure they are legitimate and originated from trusted sources.</p>
            <p>Server-side frameworks often provide built-in mechanisms for CSRF protection, which should be utilized.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <form action="/changemail" method="post">
        <input type="email" name="Email" id="email" placeholder="New Email" required>
        <button type="submit">Change Email</button>
    </form>

    <div class="corner">
        
        <a href="/change-password">Change Password</a>
        <a href="/forgotpassword">Forgot Password</a>
        <a href="/about">About</a>
        <a href="/contact">Contact</a>
    </div>

    <div class="social-icons">
        <a href="#" target="_blank"><img src="path_to_facebook_icon.png" alt="Facebook"></a>
        <a href="#" target="_blank"><img src="path_to_twitter_icon.png" alt="Twitter"></a>
        <a href="#" target="_blank"><img src="path_to_instagram_icon.png" alt="Instagram"></a>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
